title: Check your Driver CPC periodic training hours

heading_context: Check your Driver CPC periodic training hours
chunks.html_content:
Use this service to:

  • check how many hours of Driver Certificate of Professional Competence (CPC) training you’ve done
  • check which courses you’ve attended
  • check when you’ll get your next Driver CPC card
  • create a temporary password for your employer so they can view your record
  • view your employee’s record if they’ve given you a temporary password

Register to use the service if you’re a new user.
chunks.plain_content:

  view your employee’s record if they’ve given you a temporary password

heading_context: Check your Driver CPC periodic training hours
chunks.html_content: You cannot register until the training centre has recorded your first Driver CPC training course.
chunks.plain_content:
Check your Driver CPC periodic training hours
You cannot register until the training centre has recorded your first Driver CPC training course.

heading_context: Check your Driver CPC periodic training hours
chunks.html_content:
You’ll need your:

  • driving licence number

  • home postcode

A password will be sent by post to the address on your driving licence. 

If you do not receive your password letter within 3 working days and you live in England, Scotland or Wales, contact DVSA.

heading_context: Check your Driver CPC periodic training hours
chunks.html_content:
Contact the training centre if any training you’ve done is not showing on your record after 5 working days.  

If the training centre has stopped trading and they have not updated your training record, you can get help from Citizens Advice.
